Proposed implementation plan:

A. Add a camera-projection motion cache
For each camera projection coded block, compute and store motion information at 4x4 granularity.

For each 4x4 subblock:

* sample projected displacement at the four luma corner pixels
* average the four displacement vectors
* convert the averaged displacement into VTM Mv internal precision
* store:
    * MotionInfo::isInter = true
    * MotionInfo::interDir
    * MotionInfo::mv[RPL0/RPL1]
    * MotionInfo::refIdx[RPL0/RPL1]
    * MotionInfo::sliceIdx
    * MotionInfo::usesLIC = false unless the camera projection mode explicitly supports LIC

B. Modify motion buffer spanning
In PU::spanMotionInfo() or a helper called from it, add a camera-projection branch:

* if the CU uses camera projection mode:
    * do not call mb.fill(mi)
    * instead copy the precomputed 4x4 camera-projection MotionInfo into cu.getMotionBuf()
* this allows neighboring blocks to use getMotionInfo(pos) normally.

C. Regular merge support
Modify the existing logic that currently marks camera projection neighbors unavailable.
Instead:

* allow camera projection CUs as inter neighbors
* rely on puNeigh->getMotionInfo(pos) to return the 4x4 camera-projection MV at the queried position
* keep the existing MergeCtx filling logic unchanged as much as possible.

D. Affine merge support
Add a camera-projection affine candidate path.

For a camera projection block, derive 3 control-point MVs:

* LT: projected motion near the top-left corner
* RT: projected motion near the top-right corner
* LB: projected motion near the bottom-left corner

Prefer using averaged local corner samples or nearby 4x4 cache entries, not a single noisy pixel.

Then add a candidate into AffineMergeCtx:

* affMrgCtx.mvFieldNeighbours[cand][0][list] = LT
* affMrgCtx.mvFieldNeighbours[cand][1][list] = RT
* affMrgCtx.mvFieldNeighbours[cand][2][list] = LB
* affMrgCtx.interDirNeighbours[cand] = cameraProjInterDir
* affMrgCtx.affineType[cand] = AffineModel::_6_PARAMS if LT/RT/LB are all valid
* set refIdx for each list consistently
* set bcwIdx = BCW_DEFAULT
* set LICFlags = false
* run the same redundancy/similarity checks used by existing affine merge candidates where possible.

