Please use the following method to derive per-pixel MV from the camera projection tool.

Goal:
After camera projection, each current-frame pixel should have a motion vector that points to the projected position in the reference frame. This MV will later be reused for regular merge MotionInfo and affine merge control-point generation.

Definition:
For each current pixel (x_cur, y_cur), project it into the selected reference frame using the current depth and camera parameters.

If the projected reference-frame coordinate is:

(x_ref, y_ref)

then the motion vector is:

mv_x = x_ref - x_cur;
mv_y = y_ref - y_cur;

This is the same direction as a normal inter MV: from the current block/pixel position to the reference-frame sampling position.

Use backward projection, not forward splatting:
For each current pixel:

current pixel + current depth
  -> current camera-space 3D point
  -> world-space 3D point
  -> reference camera-space 3D point
  -> reference image coordinate
  -> MV = reference coordinate - current coordinate

Do not derive MV from forward-projected splat positions, because forward projection can create holes, duplicates, and ambiguous ownership. The MV cache should be defined per current pixel.

Pseudo-code:

for each current pixel (x, y):
{
    depth = getCurrentDepth(x, y);
    // 1. Back-project current pixel to 3D using current camera and depth
    P_cur_cam = unprojectCurrentPixel(x, y, depth);
    // 2. Transform current camera point to world
    P_world = curCameraToWorld * P_cur_cam;
    // 3. Transform world point to reference camera
    P_ref_cam = refWorldToCamera * P_world;
    // 4. Project to reference image plane
    (x_ref, y_ref, valid) = projectToReferenceImage(P_ref_cam);
    if (valid)
    {
        float mvx = x_ref - float(x);
        float mvy = y_ref - float(y);
        storePixelMotion(x, y, mvx, mvy);
    }
    else
    {
        markPixelMotionInvalid(x, y);
    }
}

Conversion to VTM internal MV precision:
After computing the floating-point pixel displacement, convert it to VTM MV precision.

Example:

Mv mv;
mv.hor = round(mvx * (1 << MV_FRACTIONAL_BITS_INTERNAL));
mv.ver = round(mvy * (1 << MV_FRACTIONAL_BITS_INTERNAL));

If the internal MV precision is 1/16 pel, then:

mv.hor = round(mvx * 16);
mv.ver = round(mvy * 16);

Example:
If current pixel is (100, 50) and its projected reference coordinate is (96.25, 51.5), then:

mvx = 96.25 - 100 = -3.75;
mvy = 51.5  - 50  =  1.5;

With 1/16-pel internal precision:

mv.hor = round(-3.75 * 16) = -60;
mv.ver = round( 1.5  * 16) =  24;

For bi-directional camera projection:
Compute this separately for each reference list.

L0 MV = projected position in L0 reference - current position;
L1 MV = projected position in L1 reference - current position;

Store each list independently with its own refIdx.

For 4x4 MotionInfo:
After per-pixel MV is available, create a 4x4-level MV cache.

For each 4x4 subblock, sample the four luma corner pixels:

top-left
top-right
bottom-left
bottom-right

Average their valid projected MVs:

mv4x4 = average(valid corner MVs);

Then store this as the 4x4 MotionInfo MV:

mi.isInter = true;
mi.interDir = cameraProjInterDir;
mi.refIdx[RPL0] = refIdx0;
mi.refIdx[RPL1] = refIdx1;
mi.mv[RPL0] = mv4x4_L0;
mi.mv[RPL1] = mv4x4_L1;

For affine merge control points:
Reuse the 4x4 MV cache instead of doing least-squares fitting.

Use:

CP0 / LT = top-left 4x4 MV;
CP1 / RT = top-right 4x4 MV;
CP2 / LB = bottom-left 4x4 MV;

Then fill affine merge candidate fields:

affMrgCtx.mvFieldNeighbours[cand][0][list] = MvField(mvLT, refIdx);
affMrgCtx.mvFieldNeighbours[cand][1][list] = MvField(mvRT, refIdx);
affMrgCtx.mvFieldNeighbours[cand][2][list] = MvField(mvLB, refIdx);

Use 6-parameter affine when all three control points are valid:

affMrgCtx.affineType[cand] = AffineModel::_6_PARAMS;

Important notes:

* The MV direction must be reference position - current position.
* Use backward projection per current pixel.
* Do not use forward splatting to derive MV.
* Keep invalid projection handling deterministic.
* For invalid pixels or invalid 4x4 corners, either skip that MotionInfo entry or average only valid samples.
* For merge candidate usage, make sure interDir, refIdx, and MV list fields are consistent with the current slice.
* For L1, only fill it when the slice and camera projection mode actually use L1.
* This MV cache must be derivable identically on encoder and decoder side.
